<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0">
    <teiHeader><fileDesc><titleStmt><title>President Truman to Marshal Stalin
                    
                    Copy obtained from former President Harry S.
                        Truman.</title></titleStmt><sourceDesc><bibl type="frus-volume-id">frus1945v07</bibl><bibl type="frus-document-id">d633</bibl><bibl type="frus-document-number">633</bibl><bibl type="frus-div-subtype">historical-document</bibl></sourceDesc></fileDesc><profileDesc><settingDesc><setting><date notBefore="1945-06-15T14:03:00-05:00" notAfter="1945-06-15T14:03:00-05:00"/></setting></settingDesc></profileDesc></teiHeader><text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1945-06-15T14:03:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1945-06-15T14:03:00-05:00" n="633" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d633">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">761.93/6–1545: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">President <persName type="from">Truman</persName> to <persName type="to">Marshal Stalin</persName>
                    </hi>
                    <note n="61" xml:id="d633fn61">Copy obtained from former President Harry S.
                        Truman.</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">[<placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>,] <date calendar="gregorian" when="1945-06-15T15:03:00-04:00">15 June 1945—3:03 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>292. T. V. Soong departed by airplane today for Moscow via Chungking. He will
                    arrive Moscow before July 1st to discuss details of arrangements for
                    Soviet-Chinese agreements.</p>
                <p>Ambassador Hurley has been directed<note n="62" xml:id="d633fn62">Telegram No.
                        285, June 9, <ref target="#pg_897">p. 897</ref>.</note> to inform Chiang
                    Kai-shek on June 15th of Soviet conditions and to make every effort to obtain
                    the Generalissimo’s agreement therewith. Hurley is directed to inform Chiang
                    Kai-shek that the Yalta agreement will have the support of the United States
                    Government.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Truman</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
